{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-05-01-how-to-add-calendar-in-react-js/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To add calendar in react js, you can use  component. It will add calendar in react js. Today, I am going to show you, how‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To add calendar in react js, you can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Calendar/></code> component. It will add calendar in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to add calendar in react js.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Using @natscale/react-calendar.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Using @natscale/react-calendar.</h3>\n<p>we are going to create a very simple calendar without any styling. So for this, we are going to install a new npm package. Run the below code in your terminal to install the package.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm i @natscale/react-calendar</code></p>\n<h3>Step 3: Import react component.</h3>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> useState <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Calendar <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react-calendar'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react-calendar/dist/Calendar.css'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 4: Create a Component.</h3>\n<p>you can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Calendar/></code> component to add calendar in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Calendar\n\tonChange<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>onChange<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\tvalue<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>value<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Define the add calendar example.</h3>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">react-calendar</code> and use the calender component from the installed library with <code class=\"language-text\">useState</code> variable to store values to add calendar in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> useState <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Calendar <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react-calendar'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react-calendar/dist/Calendar.css'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">App</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\t<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>value<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> onChange<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">useState</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Date</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n\t<span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n\t\t<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Calendar <span class=\"token operator\">-</span>aHoisting<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Calendar\n\t\t\t\tonChange<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>onChange<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\t\t\t\tvalue<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>value<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\t\t\t<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n\t\t<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n\t<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;calendar/></code>component and add calendar in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 480px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d99a63684472c6a5937055fee387daf1/d3be9/add-calendar.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 107.59493670886076%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRmYAAABXRUJQVlA4IFoAAADQAwCdASoUABYAPtFYpU0oJKOiMBgIAQAaCWcAAC52aBbhL3KPE4AA/u/6MAgkd5n+9gI01JCvEz1RmP4W5hbratZSYd5ZPVMnCDULa6cE0ovmJbjDMAgAAAA='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, add, calendar\"\n        title=\"React, add, calendar\"\n        src=\"/static/d99a63684472c6a5937055fee387daf1/d3be9/add-calendar.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d99a63684472c6a5937055fee387daf1/81b7c/add-calendar.webp 158w,\n/static/d99a63684472c6a5937055fee387daf1/6ea66/add-calendar.webp 315w,\n/static/d99a63684472c6a5937055fee387daf1/d3be9/add-calendar.webp 480w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to add calendar in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"May 01, 2024","description":"Example of add calendar in react js with step by step tutorial - aHoisting","social_image":{"absolutePath":"/Users/mac/Documents/hoisting/ahoisting/static/media/template/reactjs.jpg"}}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to add carousel in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2024-05-02-how-to-add-carousel-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to add chart in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2024-05-01-how-to-add-chart-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2024-05-01-how-to-add-calendar-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/2024-05-02-how-to-add-carousel-in-react-js/","nextSlug":"/blog/2024-05-01-how-to-add-chart-in-react-js/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2555585279","2714594843","3159585216"]}